    <body>
        <p>When you add an Atlassian card to a flow for the first time, you'll be prompted to configure the connection. This will enable you to connect your Atlassian account, save your account information, and reuse the connection in new flows that include Atlassian.</p>
        <p><span class="uicontrol">Note:</span> You can create multiple connections and manage them from your Settings page.</p>
        <p>To create a new connection from an Action card:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>Click <span class="uicontrol">New Connection</span>.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Enter a <span class="uicontrol">Connection Nickname</span>. This is useful if you plan to create multiple Atlassian connections to share with your team.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Enter a value in the <span class="uicontrol">API Token</span> field.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Enter a value in the <span class="uicontrol">Directory ID</span> field.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Click <span class="uicontrol">Create</span>.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>